Buy/Stream ’Satellite (Above & Beyond’s 2023 Progressive Mix): aboveandbeyond.ffm.to/satpro.pbt 
Follow Anjunabeats New Releases on Spotify: anjunabeats.co/newreleases.pbt

Release Date: 16th November 2023

Above & Beyond release their 2023 Progressive Mix of iconic OceanLab single, ‘Satellite’, out 16 November on Anjunabeats.

OceanLab is the chart-hitting side project of Above & Beyond (Jono Grant, Tony McGuinness and Paavo Siljamaki) and singer-songwriter Justine Suissa.

With a discography spanning over two decades - including top 20 UK single ‘Satellite’ (2004), two top 25 UK dance albums (‘Sirens of the Sea’ in 2008 and ‘Sirens of the Sea Remixed’ in 2009), and two top 10 UK dance singles (‘Clear Blue Water’ in 2003, and ‘Satellite’ in 2004) - OceanLab cemented themselves as a seminal dance act with an undeniably unique sound, where Justine Suissa’s compelling voice, lyrics and melodies take centre stage.

OceanLab’s ‘Satellite’ was released in 2004 to wide acclaim, peaking at number 19 in the UK singles chart in May 2004 and remaining there for a month. The track would go on to become a cult classic, sung along to by fans at countless Above & Beyond shows.

Almost twenty years on from its original release, Above & Beyond now release their 2023 Progressive Mix of ‘Satellite’, which they debuted to 22,000 fans at their Group Therapy 500 celebrations at Banc of California Stadium last year.

‘Satellite’ (Above & Beyond's 2023 Progressive Mix) is the first single from the forthcoming ‘OceanLab: The Anthology’ project, which celebrates the legacy of the iconic trance group through a series of new remixes, a digital compilation, and a limited edition vinyl box set product.

This year, Above & Beyond were the only British DJs to sell out two consecutive nights at Printworks as part of the iconic London venue’s closing season. Over the summer, their Group Therapy Weekender festival once again saw thousands of Anjunafamily descend on the Gorge Amphitheatre in Washington State. They also made appearances at Tomorrowland in Belgium and Insomniac's Electric Daisy Carnival in Las Vegas. They recently made a return to Red Rocks Amphitheatre to helm two shows alongside label stars from Anjunabeats and Anjunadeep.

Above & Beyond's next live celebrations will take place at Dreamstate festivals in California and Sydney, followed by shows at The GelreDome in The Netherlands and The Palace of Fine Arts Theatre in San Francisco. Tickets on sale now (www.aboveandbeyond.nu/tour).

OceanLab ‘Satellite’ (Above & Beyond's 2023 Progressive Mix) is out today, 16 November on Anjunabeats.

items.description:
Stream/download: https://orcd.co/notasecret

Three extremely talented artists within dance music join forces to bring you groove-laden vocal dance-pop track ‘Not A Secret’.

Italian heritage collides in epic fashion on this brand-new heater from Prezioso, Shibui and Alex Pizzuti! Each of those involved bring their individual styles on ‘Not A Secret’, each twinged with that Italian elegance and swagger. Alex Pizzuti and Prezioso create a slow, churning but extremely catchy soundscape, after which singer/songwriter Shibui intervenes and displays her musical prowess with a beautifully pitched vocal line. What your left with is a dance-pop euphoria, taking the best aspects of many styles and packaging them in to an accessible and most importantly dance-able song to welcome in the winter months on Smash The House!

Prezioso is an Italian DJ and producer who initially found recognition through his incredible skills behind a turntable and some vinyl! This turntablist career took him to local, to regional to world championships before he eventually made the leap in to solo producing and DJ’ing in a more traditional sense. In 2015, Prezioso burst on to the scene with his rework of the 80’s classic ‘The Riddle’ and furthered his arsenal of hits like ‘Thunder’ with Gabry Ponte, which has reached close to 400m streams worldwide, cementing Prezioso as a frontrunner in the scene.

Shibui is another incredibly talented artist hailing from Italy, who has taken the scene by storm with her angelic voice, poetic songwriting and even solid producing skills. Her wide range of talents have helped her work with some of the biggest best in the scene, including the likes of Vini Vici, LUM!X, Vinai, Afrojack, Blasterjaxx, Marnik, Mariana Bo and many more. Shibui’s musical prescence, combined with Prezioso’s unique production skills and topped off with newcomer Alex Pizzuti’s fresh and contemporary pockets of influence creates a real epic moment for Italian dance music!
items.title: Prezioso x Shibui x Alex Pizzuti - Not A Secret

As the official record label of melodic dubstep leader Seven Lions, Ophelia Records is a label that promotes independent dance music across a wide range of genres. In just five years, Ophelia has become one of the hottest labels in electronic music thanks to its tight-knit community and ability to connect fans of melodic bass, dubstep, trance, psytrance, drum & bass, house and beyond. Releases have picked up support on flagship playlists across DSPs and radio stations, including the cover of Spotify’s Mint, SiriusXM BPM playlisting and numerous adds to New Music Friday, Dance Rising, danceXL, Bass Arcade and more. With massive releases from acts such as SLANDER, Excision, Kill The Noise, MitiS, Jason Ross, NGHTMRE, Wooli, Trivecta, Blastoyz, Crystal Skies and Last Heroes, Ophelia has reached significant milestones with over 200 catalog releases, multiple #1 iTunes Dance records, sold out showcases and festival takeovers.
